  "text": "The physics of phase segregation is a relevant subject for discussion considering that the plasma membrane is a lipid bilayer. Several groups have focused on exploring the phase diagram of multi-component membrane systems in terms of the co-existence of liquid-ordered (l o ) and -disordered (l d ) domains [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and its relationship to what occurs at the cell membrane [CITATION_3] .",
